By: Senators James of the 28th, Rhett of the 33rd, Orrock of the 36th, Mallow of the 2nd,
Esteves of the 35th and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Dr. Kevin James; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Dr. Kevin James currently serves as the 19th president of Morris Brown
3 College, where his vision and expertise have been instrumental in restoring the institution's
4 accreditation after nearly two decades, making it the first historically Black college and
5 university to accomplish this significant achievement; and
6 WHEREAS, under his leadership, Morris Brown College secured full accreditation from the
7 Transnational Association of Christian Colleges and Schools on April 26, 2022, restoring the
8 institution's eligibility for federal financial aid programs and Title IV funding as well as
9 reinstating its participation in the Strengthening Historically Black Colleges and Universities
10 program under Title III; and
11 WHEREAS, with more than 23 years of experience as an educator, administrator, and
12 executive leader, Dr. James has spearheaded efforts to stabilize the college's finances, expand
13 academic offerings, increase fundraising, implement a five-year strategic plan, and achieve
14 record-breaking enrollment; and
