15 WHEREAS, his exemplary service extends beyond Morris Brown College through active
16 participation on the boards of the African Methodist Episcopal Church Worldwide, the
17 Georgia Hispanic Chamber of Commerce, Kappa Kappa Psi, and the Historic Oakland
18 Foundation, among others; and
19 WHEREAS, widely regarded as a leading voice in higher education, Dr. James is a
20 sought-after keynote speaker, mentor, and advocate who frequently addresses topics related
21 to historically Black colleges and universities, equity and inclusion, and the unique
22 challenges faced by minority-serving institutions; and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable individual be
24 appropriately honored during this special time.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
26 recognize and commend Dr. Kevin James for his outstanding leadership as president of
27 Morris Brown College and his dedication to higher education as well as extend best wishes
28 for continued success.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
30 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Dr. Kevin James.
